# Start here (new to Gemini)

This is a best-effort guide for getting started with Gemini. It is not official documentation.
If something is wrong or outdated, please tell us.

## 2-minute overview
Gemini is a small, text-first protocol that tries to keep things simple:
* pages are lightweight
* there is no tracking by default
* there is no client-side scripting
* the format (gemtext) is intentionally minimal

## Your first steps
1. Install a Gemini client
2. Visit a few capsules (sites) and get comfortable navigating
3. Bookmark things you like
4. When ready: publish a simple capsule of your own

=> /clients/choose-a-client.gmi Step 1: Choose a Gemini client
=> /discovery.gmi Step 2: Find things to read
=> /publishing.gmi Step 3: Learn basic gemtext
=> /hosting-first-capsule.gmi Step 4: Host your first capsule

## What this site is (and is not)
* This site is a curated map and a set of starter guides.
* This site is not “the official Gemini docs”.

## Additional curated resources
Gemini is not about a centralized, siloed, gatekeeping, community. It is a living ecosystem with a LOT of resources. The following are other resources that I have been made aware of. It will ebb and flow over time, but the goal is to let newcomers discover Geminispace, not be forced into it.

=> gemini://gemini.smallweb.space/HOWTO/index.gmi Gritty's HOWTOs

